name: Leave of Absence CD
description: The limited edition 9-song EP was originally released in 2008 on Reform School Music / Domination Recordings. Production handled by Marco Polo, Khrysis, M-Phazes, !llmind, Eric G, and The Mighty DR. Guest features by Torae, Finale, Kil Ripkin, and Dan Johns. These are the remaining stock left over after the original pressing. Get them before they are gone for good!

name: Chain Letters
description: The critically acclaimed album from Supastition which received presitious reviews XXL, The Source, Scratch, and many other publications at the time of its release in 2005. The followup to The Deadline, Chain Letters boasts the production of heavy hitters such as Jake One, Little Brother, Nicolay, M-phazes, !llmind, and many others. This is the original pressing from Soulspazm Records before the re-release by Rawkus Records.

name: Splitting Image
description: Enter the code: CLOSEOUT at checkout to receive 50% off of this item when you purchase 1 other item from the online store. Originally released as a side project recorded under Supastition's birth name, Kam Moye, this project shows a more mature side as he addresses topics such as marriage, depression, humility, and unemployment. The lead single, Let's Be Honest, received rotation on MTV and major radio airplay. Production handled by Grammy Award winning producer S1, Jake One, Vitamin D, Veterano, M-phazes, Marco Polo, and more. Guest features by Phonte, One Be Lo, Zumbi (of Zion I), Buff1, John Robinson, and others.
